<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3–746</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Soviet Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Novikov</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-12">March 12, 1946</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledgment is made of the receipt
                                of your Note dated March 7, 1946, informing me that the Soviet
                                Government shared the opinion of the French Government, that the
                                question of the situation in Spain should be submitted to the
                                Security Council.</p>
                            <p>There is enclosed a statement of the views of the Government of the
                                United States on this question, as they were communicated to the
                                French Government in Paris.<note n="43" xml:id="d717fn43">See
                                    telegram 1096, March 8, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note></p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James F.
                                Byrnes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>